               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17870523-39-person476">
                  WILLIAM
                   BELDAM
               <interp inst="t17870523-39-person476" type="surname" value="BELDAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17870523-39-person476" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17870523-39-person476" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I was not at the Three Compasses; I was coming up Peter-street, and I saw 
               <persName id="t17870523-39-person477">
                  William
                   Parker
               <interp inst="t17870523-39-person477" type="surname" value="Parker"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17870523-39-person477" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17870523-39-person477" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             running on, and the two prisoners running before him; he was calling loudly for White; just as they got to him, he caught hold of Thomas's coat, and Thomas turned round, and struck him on the right side of the head; in the mean time, White and Smith came up to him, and the other prisoner tried to get him away; we took them into a public-house, the Red Lion, the corner of Benjamin-street, and they were taken to the watch-house, and from thence to Bridewell; I saw him strike him on the side of the face, after he laid hold of his coat; he had nothing in his hand.</p>
